00:17:03.930 --> 00:17:07.589
research is predominantly
funded by government

00:17:07.589 --> 00:17:12.930
and the actors are
universities, and development

00:17:12.930 --> 00:17:15.330
is predominantly
funded by industry,

00:17:15.330 --> 00:17:17.205
which tends to be a more
incremental advance.

00:17:22.550 --> 00:17:24.859
And there's something also
that you just kind of need

00:17:24.859 --> 00:17:26.276
to keep in the
back of your minds,

00:17:26.276 --> 00:17:29.060
which is product cycle theory.

00:17:29.060 --> 00:17:31.310
That products go
through cycles--

00:17:31.310 --> 00:17:33.600
go through evolutionary stages.

00:17:33.600 --> 00:17:37.400
So a firm defines a product,
it develops a market for it,

00:17:37.400 --> 00:17:39.890
then it standardizes
the product.

00:17:39.890 --> 00:17:43.100
And then typically
over time, one design

00:17:43.100 --> 00:17:45.950
will tend to dominate.

00:17:45.950 --> 00:17:49.580
And then the number of competing
companies with varying designs

00:17:49.580 --> 00:17:52.430
will tend to shrink.

00:17:52.430 --> 00:17:55.430
And over time, the
product will sometimes

00:17:55.430 --> 00:17:58.940
become a true commodity product.

00:17:58.940 --> 00:18:01.970
High volume, the price
goes significantly down,

00:18:01.970 --> 00:18:05.570
and the profit margin
is much lower, so

00:18:05.570 --> 00:18:10.370
the uniqueness of the
product kind of ebbs.

00:18:10.370 --> 00:18:13.910
At that stage in the US
system, the production

00:18:13.910 --> 00:18:15.362
often goes offshore.

00:18:15.362 --> 00:18:17.570
That's the moment where it
occurs where the commodity

00:18:17.570 --> 00:18:19.910
production begins.

00:18:19.910 --> 00:18:22.400
Barriers to entry
increase at this point

00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:25.760
because only a modest number of
firms on a standardized product

00:18:25.760 --> 00:18:27.530
tend to dominate.

00:18:27.530 --> 00:18:31.802
And the surviving firms
have to have the capacity

00:18:31.802 --> 00:18:33.260
to keep advancing
their technology,

00:18:33.260 --> 00:18:35.210
keep making
incremental advances.

00:18:35.210 --> 00:18:37.993
They've gotta be able to
master large scale production,

00:18:37.993 --> 00:18:40.160
they've gotta have strong
distribution and marketing

00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:41.952
arms, and they've gotta
have the management

00:18:41.952 --> 00:18:45.050
talent to kind of work
across all those pieces.

