01:05:53.980 --> 01:05:56.740
So it's a longer
period, frankly,

01:05:56.740 --> 01:06:00.480
than this in many, many cases.

01:06:00.480 --> 01:06:03.750
But then after the bubble--
and in the IT world,

01:06:03.750 --> 01:06:06.870
that's the Dot-com bust of 2001.

01:06:06.870 --> 01:06:09.720
Then all kinds of dot-coms fail.

01:06:09.720 --> 01:06:12.360
And then the surviving
firms are stronger

01:06:12.360 --> 01:06:15.120
and they go on a period of
stable continued growth.

01:06:15.120 --> 01:06:17.290
I would argue that
that's where we're on now

01:06:17.290 --> 01:06:20.070
in the IT innovation wave.

01:06:20.070 --> 01:06:23.100
Eventually, we'll reach
technology maturity.

01:06:23.100 --> 01:06:27.330
The IT wave is complicated
because information

01:06:27.330 --> 01:06:31.770
is a core organizing
principle of the universe.

01:06:31.770 --> 01:06:33.340
It's like mass and energy--

01:06:33.340 --> 01:06:35.020
it's one of those big things.

01:06:35.020 --> 01:06:37.590
And if you're tying your
innovation wave to something

01:06:37.590 --> 01:06:41.190
as fundamental and powerful as
that, maybe it's more enduring.

01:06:41.190 --> 01:06:43.920
And we haven't begun to touch
artificial intelligence yet.

01:06:43.920 --> 01:06:48.270
So maybe we'll get a
lot longer run, Max,

01:06:48.270 --> 01:06:50.230
in our stable growth period--

01:06:50.230 --> 01:06:52.080
